 The statement read as follows, “An observation has been made through gathered statistics that public libraries are now experiencing an increase of up to more than 100 people per day due to learners from tertiary institutions and schools visiting libraries. ” According to the statement, this is a major health risk. Therefore, the municipalities are instructed to ensure that public libraries close with immediate effect. ALSO READ: Department of Community Services warn Mbombela resident about waste bags Library officials are still to report to the libraries, and work behind closed doors. Drop-in boxes will be put outside the libraries for users to return their borrowed books.